gen-z social media caption: I’m thrilled to be adding to the 2.3% of Black chiropractors in the US, a black woman at that. These past 7 months I have grown so much. I moved to this new city where I didn't know many people or had any family. I spent a lot of time having to remind myself that I can do this. That this is still my dream even if it wasn't what I pictured. I was denied PT school twice but God showed me that he is in control of my life, and that’s when I decided to look into the chiropractic field. I truly thank God for opening this door when others closed right in my face, my parents, family, and friends for always praying & being in my corner and encouraging me. Counting down the days until I can finally add “DC” behind my name. Dr. Westbrook Loading…. 👩🏽‍⚕️ #blackdoctors #blackchiropractors #womenchiropractors #blackfemalechiropractor #healthandwellness #adjusting #honorcodeceremony

caption: a baby is holding a baby in its arms 
gen-z social media caption: my mamaw ruthie made her way home and into heaven yesterday.. not sure i can find the words to sum up exactly how i feel. i was able to spend the last month of her life by her side and for that i’m honored and beyond lucky to have had that time together. we talked a lot, we laughed a lot, but we sometimes just sat and soaked in each others company and said nothing at all. we sang against the wind by bob seger - one of her favorites of all time. i keep going back to that moment and know now she’s no longer against the wind but inside it… she is the wind, the sun and stars, the creek that runs through the bottom of the hill, the birds and deer, and every sunset i ever watch from here on out. mamaw is in all that is good and all that is beautiful.. mamaw you are forever apart of me and i love you so much. i am so honored to be your granddaughter and to have so many of your features. from your firey personality down to your feet and eyebrows. we sat in her hospital bed and laughed at how similar our feet were. there’s no memory with you i wont cherish. we were ALL so lucky to have known, love, and admire you. adored by so many. not one soul who met my mamaw didn’t fall in love with her.. i’ll see you again and until then every song i sing, everything i do, will be for you. i hope to become even HALF of the brave, strong, and courageous woman you were. thank you for everything. i will miss you until i get to hug you and hold you again. i don’t even know how to end this cause i can’t say goodbye yet. i never will. i love you mamaw forever and ever after that

gen-z social media caption: Initially, the thought of rushing a Pre-Med fraternity made me laugh. And not going to lie, I thought they would all be a bunch of weird, nerdy, pre med kids. I cannot believe how wrong I was. Looking back on it now, rushing Mu Delta was by far the best decision I have ever made in my life. I know for a fact, I would not be pre-med still at this point in my life if it was not for these guys here. From pulling all nighters together in the library, to sitting next to each other every day in class, it kept me grounded and focused on what I needed to do to eventually become a doctor. Academics aside, Mu Delta gave me life long friendships. Who knew going through the absolute shit show of pre med classes together would forge an unbreakable bond between us. I will never forget the fun we had and especially our insane date party trips to Vegas. Mu Delta not only gave us a template to succeed career wise, but it also taught us how to be men for others. Cheers boys, until next time.

caption: a person sitting on a tree in the middle of a field 
gen-z social media caption: 10 days until The Hardest Part.. my first studio album. i’m thinking a lot about my home in nashville.. the coyotes in the distance, my dad leading me through the fields where i used to run as a little girl, the horses, the deer in the grass, the sunsets and the songs. this is where i developed much of the sonic landscape of the record and found the majority of my inspiration.. i can’t wait for you to hear it.

caption: a book with a picture of a person on it 
gen-z social media caption: THANK YOU.. i want to thank specifically the collaborators i worked with on this record.. thank you to the incredibly talented co/writers and producers <NAME> <NAME> , <NAME> <NAME> <NAME> , Britten Newbill, <NAME> <NAME> , <NAME> , <NAME> <NAME> , <NAME> .. i’ve known my friend tommy english since i was 16 and these are our first records we’ve made together that have been put out. ilsey, dan, jr, and myself started unfinished before i could drive myself to the sessions!!!! thank you to <NAME> for the countless amount of hours you spent paying such close attention to detail in every vocal, harmony, and instrument also for not losing your mind and mike and i yelling “STEPHEEEN” every 5 seconds. eating tacos with you and mike is my favorite pastime.. also a HUUUGE thank you to <NAME> for mastering every single song perfectly <3 thank you to every single musician on this album.. <NAME> , <NAME> , <NAME> ,@ross_garren ,@chrisbondmusic , <NAME> , <NAME> Camerieri , <NAME> , <NAME> , <NAME> , <NAME> ,Taylor Johnson, <NAME> , <NAME> every single one of your parts was so extremely important to create such an immersive, dynamic, atmospheric album. <NAME> and i had probably THE MOST FUN working with you guys and choosing all the most special bits and pieces of all of your guys’ beautiful work. i STILL feel as if i’ve left people out but thank you thank you thank you to every single person involved.. i’ll never be able to fully describe my gratitude.

gen-z social media caption: MY <NAME> WHITE SHOW LOOK “HER BEHEADING” my inspiration behind this look came from my deep love and fascination of Marie Antoinette. I remember watching the 2006 movie over and over again at my grandmas house when I was a child. I was obsessed with the highly stylised take on renaissance fashion and depiction of women in general. I could never understood why her final execution was so gruesome. as I got older and started to understand the politics behind her punishment, I understood she was a villain. But some of the most fascinating people are villains, I wanted to create a look that portrayed the repercussions of her need for flamboyance and materialism. I hand sewed each ruffle on the skirt imbedding a pearl between each stitch. I incorporated ribbons and bows into over half on my garment. I didn’t only look at the way The last queen of France dressed her self I looked in to every inch of her life down to what bed sheets she slept in. When it came to herself she was tremendously selfish and materialism was not enough her ego overthrew her. every fine detail was covered in gold or diamonds or pearls. In the words of Madonna she was a “material girl” A special thank you to My beautiful model <NAME> Prosthetic made by David white for the movie the Northman photo: <NAME> whoismiamin art direction: <NAME> And production <NAME> <NAME> <NAME> It’s been such a amazing experience <NAME> #bafcsm22 #centralsaintmartins #whiteshow #granary #dazedanddiscovered #thevanillaissue #bafcsm #upnextdesigner #csm

gen-z social media caption: I feel as though I have no words.. but that just isn’t true. Actually, I have so many that it’s hard to make sense of them. You were always a hard worker.. even when physically working was hard. You were diligent, you were thoughtful, loving, quiet, courageous, strong, patient and kind. These are only a few of the words that describe you. Sometimes I have people in my life who say so much and nothing at the same time. My papa was a man who said very little, but all of his words had meaning. He taught me that when you break something you fix it even better than it was before. He taught me that being a listener is just as important as being a talker. I like to pretend nothing can hurt me anymore. This hurts. This is a pain that will never go away. One time my papa told me that because of me, he would never give up. So now and forever, because of him, I will never give up either. I can do anything. And I will do it with him in my heart. My favorite holiday growing up was the 4th of July, because that’s my Papas birthday. I love you Papa. I love you more than you loved old cars, music, western shows, wheel of fortune, coconut cream pie, the Frio River and beer. This year, I’ll be missing you on my birthday. I wish I could have one more hug from you. God is so lucky to have you. I will miss you more and more every single day. "May there be comfort in knowing that someone so special will never be forgotten." -Julie Hebert
